      "tileFilter": {},
      "isAutoRefreshDisabled": false,
      "markdown": "# How to use it\n\nUse wit Data Explorer, SLO or Metric event where metric selector allow expressions. It works by multiplying the expresion with a value of the business level (typically 1) and outside business hours by a non-existent value.\n\n## Simple example\n\nJust multiply with the desired business hour level:\n\nbuiltin:host.cpu.user:splitBy():auto * business_hours:filter(eq(level,\"8x5\")):splitBy():auto\n\n## Combining levels\n\nYou can combine multiple levels by applying another level. To use negatives, use the feature **generate negative** for generating also negative levels (prefixed by - )\n\nbuiltin:host.cpu.user:splitBy():auto * business_hours:filter(eq(level,\"16x7\")):splitBy():auto * business_hours:filter(eq(level,\"-deploywindow\")):splitBy():auto"
    }
